Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.23,0:00:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I am the Guardian of Time".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.53,0:00:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And to the foolish woman who commits\Nblasphemy against time's flow...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.99,0:00:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"As punishment, in the instant you were born into this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I shall put an end to your allotted time by way of a formless sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.83,0:00:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"From: The Guardian of Time."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.09,0:00:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, say...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.09,0:00:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this letter threatening a murder!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.48,0:00:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.76,0:00:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Starting two years ago, we've been receiving this\Nletter every year as the mistress's birthday nears.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.76,0:00:31.59,Signs,,0,0,0,,Oume Gakumichi (42)\NHoshina Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Always from an unidentified sender.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.77,0:00:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since it started two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean nothing happened to the\Nmistress last year or the year before?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.90,0:00:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.90,0:00:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were able to complete both of her\Nbirthday parties without incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.69,0:00:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, because the mistress already\Nspoke about the letter to her guests...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The number of guests coming to the birthday\Nparty has been decreasing each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.25,0:01:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's why you'd like me, Mouri Kogorou,\Nto uncover the sender of these letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.25,0:01:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.17,0:01:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If possible, we'd like for you to come to\Nthe mistress's 50th birthday party...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.30,0:01:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And perhaps even serve as a sort of bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.39,0:01:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A quinquagenarian woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.60,0:01:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, as far as bodyguarding goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.68,0:01:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've prepared this amount to cover your retainer fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Case accepted!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.24,0:01:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.16,0:01:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.24,0:01:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does the "blasphemy against\Ntime's flow" part in the letter mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.79,0:01:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that mean to disobey or disgrace time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.42,0:01:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, does that mean the mistress is really loose about time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.75,0:01:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.17,0:01:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.59,0:01:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.58,0:01:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like fog clearing up in a swoosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see through both romance and cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:01:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A threat that stops time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.23,0:02:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Terror rampages during a birthday party!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.48,0:02:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.39,0:03:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're late by 2 minutes and 17 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.35,0:04:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we not agree to meet at precisely 1430 hours, Detective Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.31,0:04:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.64,0:04:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite a long way here from the garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it was raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.15,0:04:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Human life has a limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:16.03,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hoshina Rukako (50)\NHead the Hoshina Family
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I make it a point to not waste even one second!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.82,0:04:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Oume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock in the study is slow by nearly one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.29,0:04:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.08,0:04:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall see that it is fixed at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She rules overtime as if she were the "Goddess of Time" herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.55,0:04:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as people need their days off...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.07,0:04:43.60,Signs,,0,0,0,,Karube Teigo (45)\NArchitect
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.30,0:04:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better to relax and allow your\Nclocks some time to catch their breath?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, clocks have no blood coursing through them...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:50.69,Signs,,0,0,0,,Suou Chiaki (39)\NInterior Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.48,0:04:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they have no need for rest as we humans do, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrongâ€”they're the same as humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.63,0:04:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as humans need checkups, if we neglect\Nto occasionally inspect and oil our clocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll soon rust and find it hard to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Clocks continue working even as we humans sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:08.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Furagaki Rinsaku (64)\NClock Technician
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.16,0:05:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wear down their gears as they indicate the time\Nand even their springs gradually weaken, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.92,0:05:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, these people must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who planned this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.47,0:05:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who took care of the interior design...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one who constructed the great\Nclock attached to this house, Furugaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.52,0:05:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are all guests for tonight's birthday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only came to check on the condition of that great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your birthday part is merely an aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.36,0:05:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me, I'll let myself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.24,0:05:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, I promised an old friend of mine that\NI'd look after that great clock as long as I lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.08,0:05:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"An old friend"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's referring to a clock technician that I used to employ.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.13,0:05:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impeccable gentleman who, until\Nhis accidental death four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.34,0:05:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Took care of just about every clock in this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.51,0:06:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was your elder brother, if I'm not mistaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.22,0:06:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.39,0:06:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was also my brother's recommendation that\Npermitted me to do the interior design here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right, Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.56,0:06:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I happened to come across a rather fabulous carpet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you care to see a sample?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.65,0:06:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.98,0:06:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.11,0:06:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's not just stand here and talkâ€”please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.74,0:06:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would be glad to take your umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.66,0:06:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.99,0:06:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.45,0:06:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.62,0:06:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mine's a foldable type.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall take good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.92,0:06:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an impressive number of clocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.59,0:06:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you purchase all of these yourself, Mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.60,0:06:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.72,0:06:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband, who passed away from illness\Nlast year, often complained about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.81,0:06:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd say it's as if he married a bunch of clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.19,0:06:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it is true that I am enchanted by clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By these charming tick-tock sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.45,0:07:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the sounds that play when the long hands point straight up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.41,0:07:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.71,0:07:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite magnificent when they all chime together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.59,0:07:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.63,0:07:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's so lively that I feel like I'm in an amusement park!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.30,0:07:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the clocks is slow by 0.5 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.62,0:07:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.06,0:07:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sincere apologies!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will see that it is fixed immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this is the case, make sure that the technicians are aware!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all of these clocks don't chime at my exact birth\Ntime of 6:00 PM, I will fire every last one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.44,0:07:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Duly noted!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.74,0:07:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no surprise that only your brother\Ncould be trusted to calibrate the clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hired as many as three people to fill his position after his death...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:08:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet each week I find that one or two clocks slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.88,0:08:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But not the great clock that's attached to this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.84,0:08:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only been off a handful of times in the past ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.26,0:08:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's only natural given that the maker of the\Nclock himself comes to maintain it each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is quite an impressive sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what this door's for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.37,0:08:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this great clock also has a dial facing the backyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.67,0:08:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the man from before...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's he praying toward the well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.09,0:08:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that's where the deadly fall took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My elder brother, who was the former clock technician here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.55,0:08:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was blown away by the wind while\Nrepairing the dial on this great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.89,0:08:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That well was here from before we rebuilt this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's dangerous, I've arranged to have\Nworkers come and fill it in next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.23,0:09:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I suppose I'll go offer my prayers later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.90,0:09:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he was a childhood friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, please pass along,my prayers as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not going yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are his sister, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.21,0:09:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already prayed at his grave this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since today is the anniversary of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the date he died on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had an accident on the mistress's birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.01,0:09:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll discuss the details in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.97,0:09:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I would also like Detective Mouri to find\Nthe sender of those threatening letters for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.96,0:10:01.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.96,0:10:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she never got to tell you anything about that accident, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.59,0:10:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.75,0:10:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did share a lot of detail about those who\Nheld grudges against her at work, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sender referred to themselves\Nas the "Guardian of Time," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.22,0:10:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a clock technician also be a guardian of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.15,0:10:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, are you saying one of the three currently\Nemployed clock technicians could be the sender?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.53,0:10:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just stating an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bu if you put it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.20,0:10:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A woman so strict about time is more befitting\Nof the title "Guardian of Time," isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.99,0:10:40.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.83,0:10:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's caught my interest for quite some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.38,0:10:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind me taking a look at your gold watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.92,0:10:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, be my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.47,0:10:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.51,0:10:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.79,0:11:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The silver pocket watch you had before was\Nlovely, but this one suits you as well, Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.52,0:11:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a one-of-a-kind timepiece specially\Nordered from a Swiss craftsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having been replaced on a whim and then relegated to\Nrusting in a drawer, I feel sorry for the previous watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.74,0:11:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need not worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is no longer in my possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.63,0:11:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It broke, so I got rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.49,0:11:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.85,0:11:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.93,0:11:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.15,0:11:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, so it's just for blowing out\Nthe candles on the birthday cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.46,0:12:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, what's the meaning of this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.43,0:12:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did someone flee out the window!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:25.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.31,0:12:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone turn on the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.75,0:12:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan Episode 632\NFansub Release by DCTP\NRipped by DJ VK & Innushka
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.48,0:12:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As she was blowing out the candles on her birthday cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.94,0:12:51.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And soon after the room became dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone stabbed the owner of this mansion,\NHoshina Rukako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, in the chest with a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.91,0:13:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, within a matter of seconds, with the weapon\Nin tow, and before the lights came back on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.71,0:13:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They fled though a window looking\Nout over the backyard, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.42,0:13:08.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.21,0:13:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.21,0:13:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the blood splatter on the ground\Nfrom when the mistress was stabbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See the area here where the blood was obstructed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.55,0:13:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is proof that someone was standing here when\Nthey removed the weapon used for stabbing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And became drenched with a large amount of blood splatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.44,0:13:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, disregarding the fact that some guests in this\Nroom do have some amount of blood on them...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.86,0:13:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not a single person was splattered with blood to that extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.97,0:13:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, there are traces of blood that appear to have rubbed\Nagainst the window frame and the balcony handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.16,0:13:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit, drenched in blood, fled through that\Nwindow, and there's no doubt about it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.87,0:13:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.79,0:13:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were the case, something that should be present is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.76,0:13:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had been raining until the evening\Nand the ground had been muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.84,0:14:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They should've been distinctly left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.99,0:14:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's footprints, I mean, from when\Nthey leapt from this balkony and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.27,0:14:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.77,0:14:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's coming down again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.76,0:14:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.15,0:14:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it true that the culprit didn't leave behind any footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that the sender of that threatening letter was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock technician who passed away four years ago!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.75,0:14:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would a dead person go around sending letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.35,0:14:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.46,0:14:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the sender's name the "Guardian of Time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And isn't a clock technician also a guardian of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about a threatening letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.60,0:14:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they've been delivered\Nto the victim for the past two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.14,0:14:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the instant you were born into this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.23,0:14:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I shall put an end to your allotted time by\Nway of a formless sword," said the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the instant she was born into the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems 6:00 PM earlier in the night was\Nthe same as the victim's time of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And every year she also blows out the candles at precisely 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.54,0:15:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the clock technician who died four years\Nago hold a grudge against the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.79,0:15:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know the details, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he died in an accident on this\Nexact day, the mistress's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.51,0:15:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't just die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.23,0:15:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By that cold-blooded woman who ruled over\Ntime as if she were some kind of goddess!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.79,0:15:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a terrible storm that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.65,0:15:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That clock technician was doing repairs on the dial\Nof the great clock while attached to a lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:43.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the gust buffeted him so much that he fell\Ninto the well at the foot of the great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.58,0:15:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was an accident, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.16,0:15:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been just an ordinary, careless accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only she had delayed the start of her birthday party...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.92,0:15:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And gone to search for the clock technician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:16:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, she went ahead with the party\Neven though someone was missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.34,0:16:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.18,0:16:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, it wasn't until the next\Nmorning that his body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.64,0:16:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the police, it appeared he\Ndrowned to death during the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the well having water inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.23,0:16:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if someone else had gone to look for\Nmy brother, he might have been saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.27,0:16:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once the party started, things got extremely busy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.11,0:16:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any time left to find someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-lnspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Apparantly the one who held the deepest grudge against\Nthe victim was indeed that dead clock technician...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.54,0:16:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.90,0:16:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.17,0:16:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit was that person's ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.59,0:16:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's why there weren't any footprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.15,0:16:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, that ghost sure had bad eyesight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.37,0:16:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the mistress's necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It glows in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.98,0:16:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fluorescent paint must be on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.69,0:16:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was done so that they would know exactly\Nwhere the mistress was, even in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:16:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.96,0:17:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who touched the necklace?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.03,0:17:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the party, she allowed many people to touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.16,0:17:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this birthday party was also the unveiling\Nof the new accessories the mistress had bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, she also showed off and\Nhad people touch her golden pocket watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.25,0:17:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guest with fluorescent paint on\Ntheir fingers is the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.88,0:17:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I were the culprit, I'd have\Nalready washed it off in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.39,0:17:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would've been nice if we could narrow it down to a\Nfew people with the fingerprints on the necklace...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.35,0:17:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I believe many people touched it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.27,0:17:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's so dumb, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.77,0:17:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ghosts wouldn't leave fingerprints if they touched something!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, they can float through the air like wind\Nand flee without anyone having seen them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the dumb one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.91,0:17:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no reason a ghost would have to deliberately use\Nfluorescent paint in order to stab someone in the dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.67,0:17:57.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.08,0:17:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any footprints from anyone having fled, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't a ghost, then the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.05,0:18:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must have made it seem as if they had\Nescaped but is still here among us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.26,0:18:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone planted blood on the balcony\Nrailing and the window frame in advance...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.23,0:18:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And made it seem as if they had\Nopened the window and fled outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the fact the culprit hasn't gone outside means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.23,0:18:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The long, sharp weapon akin to an ice\Npick used to stab the victim's heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.53,0:18:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might still be hidden somewhere on their person!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, if you would please allow us to take your statements\None by one in a separate room while we search your persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.54,0:18:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you explain the blood splatter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to what you said, shouldn't a large\Namount of it have been sprayed onto the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.34,0:18:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.84,0:18:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without that problem being cleared up, I wouldn't\Ncare to undergo questioning or a body search.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.93,0:18:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.15,0:18:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are they searching us when we're not suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.94,0:18:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that rude?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.31,0:19:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, it's just for the sake of being thorough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.36,0:19:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but I've got matters to attend to, so I'll be leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.22,0:19:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.49,0:19:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.20,0:19:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.62,0:19:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A person has just died, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.71,0:19:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone had come today in order to\Ncelebrate the mistress's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.67,0:19:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the culprit who killed her might be among us...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be right to cooperate with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, the ghost of the clock technician\Nas well as my childhood friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might end up being made out to be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.61,0:19:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're the architect...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.77,0:19:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name's Karube.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I designed this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have blood on your hands and your shirt cuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.95,0:19:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have gotten there when I rushed to\Nthe mistress's side when she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no blood on me other than that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.09,0:20:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.17,0:20:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, did you notice anything at the time of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.78,0:20:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I think I heard a sound\Nlike cloth rubbing together approaching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.22,0:20:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the culprit was a woman in a dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.75,0:20:21.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, the tip of that pipe of yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks long and sharp to me, so would you allow us to examine it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.65,0:20:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.45,0:20:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, you're way out of line!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.37,0:20:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true the clock technician who\Ndied four years ago was my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.69,0:20:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that I'm likely to have the strongest motive...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.75,0:20:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was just an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.08,0:20:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I held no grudge against the mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.04,0:20:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.46,0:20:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were in charge of the mansion's interior design, Suou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, you could have set up any number of tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.93,0:20:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same could be said of Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the architect,\Nand Furugaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who constructed that great clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But probably not Furugaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who's getting on in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.98,0:21:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the culprit stabbed the mistress, they moved\Nquite nimbly and brushed up against my left side!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.40,0:21:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So here, you can see traces of blood\Nhaving rubbed off on my left arm, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.45,0:21:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's that you have stuck in your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An ornate hairpin my brother bought me a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.33,0:21:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind if we examined it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.88,0:21:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it to your heart's content!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you have return it to me later!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.43,0:21:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like those in historical dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.39,0:21:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no blade inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.73,0:21:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.77,0:21:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock craftsman who constructed that great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.82,0:21:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm Furugaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.78,0:21:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that you have a little blood\Nthat flew onto your right shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.20,0:22:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it was because that woman was stabbed to the right of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.95,0:22:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like an extensively well-used cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.87,0:22:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you been using it for a long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.79,0:22:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.83,0:22:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a cane that the clock technician we\Nspoke of earlier gave to me ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.63,0:22:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for your information, I think the\Nculprit was a pretty plump fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.39,0:22:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was pushed right before that women let out a scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.56,0:22:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By a soft, springy body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.11,0:22:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit should be among the people in the grand hall back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.11,0:22:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who in the world is this culprit that considers\Nthemselves the "Guardian of Time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.19,0:24:02.08,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.61,0:24:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.02,0:24:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That "Guardian of Time" really passed through here...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.58,0:24:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.69,0:24:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.94,0:24:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Round and round I go...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.25,0:24:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was indeed on the verge of falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.44,0:24:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Into the cunning scheme...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.67,0:24:21.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Set up by the culprit snickering in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.33,0:24:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,THE GUARDIAN OF TIME'S SWORD\N(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.92,0:24:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.34,0:24:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Clock Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.18,0:24:54.81,Adds,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.44,0:24:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.29,0:24:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is the Time Stopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.92,0:24:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that hack deduction!
